<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-09-18T06:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-09-18T06:00:00-05:00" n="152" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d152">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.2300/2: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Child</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rome</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-09-18T12:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">September 18,
                                        1923—noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 3:11
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>118. Department’s unnumbered instructions July 18.<note n="88" xml:id="d152fn88">See footnote 85, <ref target="#pg_227">p.
                                    227</ref>.</note> Foreign Office advises Italian Government will
                            be glad to furnish American officer with all information and data he may
                            require for fulfillment of mission in connection with preparations for
                            round-the-world flight of Army aeroplanes.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Child</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>